OL,5,FThe barrister continued: "This trial
OL,6,Fconcerns how Mr Bryson's evidence came
OL,7,Fto be presented to this particular
OL,8,Fcommittee, which was aware from his
OL,9,Finitial communications that his
OL,10,Fevidence had the potential to stray
OL,11,Foutwith the carefully-crafted terms of
OL,12,Freference and trespass into the realms
OL,13,Fof the ongoing NCA (National Crime
OL,14,FAgency) investigation.
OL,16,F"This particular committee adopted a
OL,17,Fdemocratic procedure to decide whether
OL,18,Fthat evidence would be presented in
OL,19,Fprivate or public session.
OL,26,@mD@ZOUxD@AOU
