OL,5,F"It is the prosecution's case that by
OL,6,Fengaging in this subterfuge to allow
OL,7,FMr Bryson to make allegations that he
OL,8,Fwell knew did not come within the
OL,9,Fterms of reference of the committee,
OL,10,FDaithi McKay, as a public office
OL,11,Fholder was wilfully misconducting
OL,12,Fhimself to such a degree as to amount
OL,13,Fto an abuse of the public trust in the
OL,14,Foffice holder's position and it was
OL,15,Fdone without reasonable excuse or
OL,16,Fjustification.
OL,26,@mD@AOU
